This location needs better training and staffing. The last time I called, Kiara hung up on me, and again she is the manager and hangs up on a customer!? Disrespectful and unprofessional. I love Jimmy John's for their delicious sandwich and their motto "Freaky Fast". I moved to St. Louis downtown a few weeks ago and called the trusted sandwich place. However, this St. Louis downtown branch was far disappointing to me. It took forever to deliver my sandwiches; It seems like they are short of delivery guys all the time. The average waiting hour would fall around between 30 m and 1 h. Many times during their business hours, they just don't even bother picking up their phone. Even when they do receive phone calls by scarce chance, they could not possibly be any more rude. When you ask them nicely to repeat what they said, they get very hysterical and start yelling at you. The employees don't even know which month September was so I had to repeat my credit card number over and over. I guess he didn't know September would be 09 on the card. My overall experience with this store? VERY BAD.
